BACKGROUND: The use of Indwelling Pleural Catheter (IPC) in the care of patients 
with Malignant Pleural Effusion (MPE) is well established, however studies 
involving public health systems of low and middle-income countries are still 
lacking. This study aimed to determine the effect of IPC on the respiratory 
symptoms and Quality of Life (QoL) of patients with MPE in the setting of a 
Brazilian public health system.
METHODS: From August 2015 to November 2019, patients with MPE underwent IPC 
placement and were prospectively followed. QoL and respiratory symptoms were 
assessed by the EORTC questionnaires (QLQ-30; LC13) and Visual Analogue Scale 
