most common complication and all patients recovered with appropriate 
antimicrobial therapy. QoL did not change significantly over time, however, the 
VAS showed a significant improvement in dyspnea (+1.2: -0.5; p = 0.001).
CONCLUSION: IPC relieves respiratory symptoms without compromising the QoL, with 
a low complication rate. It represents a suitable option for patients with MPE 
and short LE in an emerging country.

