were estimated in 2019 according to ASRs. The global number of mortality and 
DALYs among males accounted for over 95% of all in 2019. Both age-sex-specific 
mortality and DALY rate were increasing with aging and reached their peak at 
85-89 age group. During the past 30 years, ASR of mortality and DALYs showed a 
decreasing trend with average annual percentage change at -3.0% [95% Confidence 
Intervals (CI): - 3.2, - 2.9] and - 2.0 (95% CI: - 1.7, - 2.2), respectively.
CONCLUSIONS: Silicosis remains an important health issue and causes a 
potentially serious burden worldwide. Attention should be paid to making 
